A%2F%2Fplanet.outlookindia.com%2Fnews%2Findia-needs-903-gwh-of-energy-storage-to-decarbonise-its-mobility-and-power-sectors-by-2030-study-news-414862%5C%22%3E903%20GWh%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20decarbonise%20just%20its%20mobility%20and%20power%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFailure%20to%20manufacture%20these%20batteries%20locally%20will%20result%20in%20huge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chemistryworld.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-battery-industry-plans-running-down-as-britishvolt-fails%2F4017099.article%5C%22%3Eimport%20dependence%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fa%3Eif%20not%20on%20China%20then%20on%20global%20commodity%20traders%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Fnews%2Fglencore-stake-stillwater-critical%2F%5C%22%3EGlencore%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Fnews%2Ftrafigura-financing-congo-cobalt%2F%5C%22%3ETrafigura%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20dominate%20trade%20in%20critical%20minerals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20problem.%20As%20Covid-19%20showed%2C%20over-reliance%20on%20any%20country%2Fcompany%20for%20critical%20supplies%20can%20result%20in%20supply%20disruptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompounding%20matters%2C%20relations%20between%20China%20and%20India%20are%20souring%20and%2C%20as%20history%20keeps%20telling%20us%2C%20control%20over%20energy%20is%20a%20powerful%20geopolitical%20weapon.%20Indeed%2C%20as%20this%20article%20was%20being%20written%2C%20in%20retaliation%20over%20semiconductor%20curbs%20by%20the%20USA%2C%20China%20restricted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fchina-restricts-exports-of-two-metals-used-in-high-performance-chips-a649402b%5C%22%3Eexports%20of%20gallium%20and%20germanium%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94both%20key%20for%20semiconductor%20manufacturing.%20Incidentally%2C%20days%20after%20this%20announcement%2C%20one%20possible%20fallout%20emerged%20from%20India.%20Foxconn%20announced%20that%20it%20was%20officially%20withdrawing%20from%20its%20%2419.5%20billion%20joint%20venture%20with%20Vedanta%20to%20produce%20semiconductors%20and%20microchips%20in%20India.%20This%20is%20undoubtedly%20a%20big%20blow%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20itself%2C%20while%20hailed%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20semi-conductor%20mission%20and%20domestic%20manufacturing%20push%2C%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20controversy.%20The%20proposed%20location%20of%20the%20manufacturing%20facility%20was%20shifted%20to%20Gujarat%20in%202021%20from%20its%20original%20location%20in%20Maharashtra%20soon%20after%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Maharashtra%20state%20government.%20While%20Foxconn%E2%80%99s%20statement%20remains%20silent%20on%20the%20reasons%20of%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20project%2C%20the%20timing%20draws%20questions%20around%20the%20impact%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20recently%20imposed%20restrictions%20on%20gallium%20and%20germanium%20exports%E2%80%94and%20by%20extension%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20self-reliance%20ambitions.%20Despite%20the%20volte-face%20maintained%20by%20both%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20and%20Vedanta%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20face%20in%20the%20immediate%20aftermath%20is%20palpable.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERacing%20to%20catch%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20create%20an%20indigenous%20renewables%20value%20chain%2C%20India%20needs%20to%20secure%20supplies%20of%20critical%20minerals%2C%20no%20less%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fgovt-unveils-first-ever-critical-minerals-list-lithium-among-30-identified-123062800967_1.html%5C%22%3E30%3C%2Fa%3E%20elements%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newly%20released%20critical%20mineral%20policy.%20The%20catch%20is%3A%20India%20is%20self-sufficient%20in%20few%20of%20these.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20critical%20mineral%20policy%E2%80%94which%20maps%20mineral%20requirements%20for%20a%20clutch%20of%20sectors%20including%20renewables%2C%20defence%2C%20electronics%2C%20telecommunications%20and%20transportation%E2%80%94lists%2010%20minerals%20where%20India%20entirely%20relies%20on%20imports.%20These%20are%20lithium%2C%20cobalt%2C%20nickel%2C%20vanadium%2C%20niobium%2C%20germanium%2C%20rhenium%2C%20beryllium%2C%20tantalum%2C%20and%20strontium.%20Others%E2%80%94like%20antimony%2C%20titanium%20and%20copper%E2%80%94are%20found%20in%20India%20but%20known%20reserves%20are%20less%20than%20the%20volumes%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcsep.org%2Fworking-paper%2Fcritical-minerals-for-india-2023%2F%5C%22%3Eworking%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20New%20Delhi-based%20Centre%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Progress%20(CSEP)%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20reserves%20of%20nickel%2C%20cobalt%2C%20molybdenum%2C%20rare%20earths%2C%20neodymium%20and%20indium%2C%20and%20the%20needs%20for%20copper%20and%20silver%20are%20higher%20than%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20current%20reserves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%20backdrop%2C%20there%20is%20rising%20clamour%20that%20India%20%3Cem%3Emust%3C%2Fem%3E%20secure%20its%20critical%20mineral%20supplies.%20Mere%20days%20after%20notifying%20the%20critical%20mineral%20policy%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Union%20Cabinet%20of%20ministers%20reportedly%20approved%20amendments%20to%20the%20Mines%20and%20Minerals%20(Development%20and%20Regulation)%20Act%20to%20allow%20the%20commercial%20mining%20of%20six%20minerals.%20Five%20of%20these%E2%80%94lithium%2C%20beryllium%2C%20titanium%2C%20niobium%2C%20and%20tantalum%E2%80%94are%20among%20those%20whose%20domestic%20production%20capacity%20is%20currently%20non-existent%20or%20significantly%20below%20requirement.%20The%20amendment%20reportedly%20goes%20even%20further%2C%20allowing%20for%20companies%20to%20suggest%20areas%20for%20exploration%20and%20extraction%E2%80%94a%20stark%20departure%20from%20established%20norms%20where%20the%20government%20identifies%20and%20auctions%20mineral%20blocks%20(as%20is%20the%20case%20with%20commercial%20coal%20mining).%20The%20amendment%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20Parliament%20during%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%2C%20which%20is%20slated%20to%20commence%20on%20July%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20odds%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20keenness%20to%20enter%20the%20critical%20minerals%20fray%20has%20been%20evident%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now%2C%20and%20the%20recent%20flurry%20of%20developments%20have%20hardly%20materialised%20from%20thin%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20the%20country%20set%20up%20KABIL%20(Khanij%20Bidesh%20India%20Ltd).%20Like%20ONGC%20Videsh%20(OVL)%2C%20which%20offsets%20India%E2%80%99s%20small%20domestic%20oil%20reserves%20by%20investing%20in%20oilfields%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20KABIL%20has%20to%20secure%20India%E2%80%99s%20supplies%20of%20strategic%20minerals%20through%20global%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20success%2C%20however%2C%20hinges%20on%20two%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20global%20geopolitics%20around%20critical%20minerals.%20Not%20only%20has%20India%20staged%20a%20belated%20entry%20into%20the%20critical%20minerals%20space%E2%80%94China%20began%20amassing%20critical%20mineral%20reserves%20from%20the%20early%202000s%3B%20and%20had%20begun%20developing%20its%20renewables%20industry%20by%20the%20end%20of%20that%20decade%E2%80%94India%20is%20also%20entering%20this%20arena%20at%20a%20time%20global%20critical%20mineral%20supply%20chains%20are%20seeing%20extraordinary%20competition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20lithium%20ion%20capacity%2C%20to%20take%20one%20instance%2C%20is%20projected%20to%20spike%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.woodmac.com%2Fpress-releases%2Fglobal-lithium-ion-battery-capacity-to-rise-five-fold-by-2030%2F%5C%22%3E1%2C000%20GWh%20in%202021%20to%205%2C500%20GWh%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202030.%20That%20works%20out%20to%20a%20demand%20of%205%2C500%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20lithium.%20To%20put%20that%20in%20perspective%2C%20global%20production%20of%20lithium%20stood%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F01%2Fchart-countries-produce-lithium-world%2F%5C%22%3E84%2C000%20tonnes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021.%20That%20is%20the%20geopolitical%20context%20in%20which%20KABIL%20has%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20factor%20is%20equally%20consequential.%20Securing%20critical%20mineral%20supplies%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20insulate%20the%20country%20from%20supply%20risks.%20If%20Chinese%20EV%20firms%20reprise%20their%20country%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20solar%20panels%E2%80%94or%20if%20Indian%20firms%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-06-08%2Fmodi-s-make-in-india-goal-relies-on-china-factories-for-supplies%3Fsref%3DzsRxy7Ix%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3Econtinue%20sourcing%20components%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20opposed%20to%20buying%20them%20from%20Indian%20manufacturers%E2%80%94the%20country%E2%80%99s%20dependence%20on%20Chinese%20supply%20chains%20will%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20to%20meaningfully%20insulate%20itself%2C%20India%20has%20to%20develop%20its%20own%20EV%20value%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20are%20these%20pieces%20coming%20together%3F%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20next%20installations%20in%20this%20series%20will%20attempt%20to%20answer%20this%20and%20paint%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20scramble%20for%20a%20place%20in%20the%20supply%20chains%20of%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fdigging-into-indias-critical-minerals-dash%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2F%5C%22%3ECarbon%20Copy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690449036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27134805%2Fpaul-alain-hunt-na_-KsSDFyQ-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdigging-into-indias-dash-for-critical-minerals%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20first%20instalment%20of%20a%20three-part%20series%20that%20explores%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20bolster%20its%20position%20in%20the%20critical%20minerals%20supply%20chains%2C%20CarbonCopy%20finds%20that%20its%20success%20depends%20on%20more%20than%20just%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20navigation%20of%20global%20geopolitics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdigging-into-indias-dash-for-critical-minerals%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%209.6%20Lakh%20Posts%20Vacant%20Across%20Ministries%20and%20Departments%2C%20Says%20Union%20Govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27112500%2FUntitled-design-11.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Close%20to%2010%20lakh%20posts%20are%20vacant%20across%20Union%20government%20ministries%20and%20departments%2C%20the%20government%20has%20said%20in%20an%20answer%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20response%20to%20an%20unstarred%20question%20by%20Trinamool%20Congress%20and%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20MPs%20Mala%20Roy%20and%20Nama%20Nageswara%20Rao%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20and%20Pensions%2C%20and%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%2C%20Jitendra%20Singh%2C%20said%20that%20as%20on%20March%201%2C%202023%2C%20there%20were%20964%2C359%20vacant%20posts%20across%20government%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20wrote%20that%20these%20figures%20are%20as%20per%C2%A0the%20annual%20report%20of%20the%20Pay%20Research%20Units%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MPs%20had%20asked%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20for%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ea)%20details%20of%20the%20total%20vacant%20posts%20that%20existed%20in%20government%20departments%2C%20including%20corporations%20and%20other%20government%20agencies%20across%20the%20country%20during%20the%20past%2010%20years%20as%20on%20June%2030%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(b)%20whether%20all%20the%20vacancies%20were%20filled%20up%20during%20the%20past%20ten%20years%2C%20if%20so%2C%20the%20details%20thereof%2C%20year-wise%20and%20if%20not%2C%20the%20reasons%20therefor%3B%20and%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(c)%20the%20action%20taken%2Fproposed%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20fill%20up%20all%20the%20vacancies%20and%20the%20time%20by%20which%20the%20recruitment%20will%20be%20completed%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%E2%80%99s%20reply%20said%20that%20the%20central%20ministries%2C%20departments%2C%20central%20public%20sector%20undertakings%2C%20autonomous%20bodies%20(including%20health%20and%20education%20institutes%2C%20public%20sector%20banks%2C%20etc.)%20recruit%20employees%20%E2%80%9Ceither%20directly%20or%20through%20recruitment%20agencies%E2%80%9D%20like%20the%20Staff%20Selection%20Commission%2C%20Union%20Public%20Service%20Commission%2C%20Railway%20Recruitment%20Board%2C%20Institute%20of%20Banking%20Personnel%20Selection%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20response%20claimed%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfilling%20up%20of%20vacant%20posts%20in%20various%20ministries%20and%20departments%20is%20a%20continuous%20process.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20part%20of%20Rozgar%20Mela%2C%20the%20vacant%20posts%20are%20being%20filled%20in%20a%20Mission%20Mode.%20Rozgar%20Mela%20events%20are%20being%20held%20across%20the%20country%20and%20the%20new%20appointees%20are%20being%20inducted%20into%20various%20Central%20Ministries%2F%20Departments%2F%20Central%20Public%20Sector%20Undertakings%20(CPSUs)%2F%20Autonomous%20Bodies%2F%20Public%20Sector%20Banks%20etc.%2C%E2