Figure%201).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%201%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20demographic%20cohort%20would%20be%20bigger%20than%20China%E2%80%99s%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023%2C%20China%20will%20still%20have%20a%20bigger%20working%20age%20population%20(those%20aged%2015-64)%20for%20another%20two%20years.%20It%20is%20only%20in%202025%20that%20there%20will%20be%20more%20people%20aged%20between%2015-64%20in%20India%20(994.7%20million)%20than%20in%20China%20(987.4%20million).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20people%20in%20the%20working%20age%20group%20are%20in%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20which%20comprises%20employed%20individuals%20and%20those%20willing%20to%20work%20but%20not%20employed%20(i.e.%2C%20unemployed).%20For%20that%20we%20must%20look%20at%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%2C%20or%20LFPR.%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPRs%20are%20not%20only%20much%20below%20the%20global%20average%2C%20but%20significantly%20lower%20than%20China%E2%80%99s.%20As%20of%202021%20(the%20latest%20year%20for%20which%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.TLF.ACTI.ZS%5C%22%3Ecomparable%20data%20is%20available%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%2075.8%20percent%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20working%20age%20population%20(15-64)%20was%20part%20of%20its%20labour%20force%20i.e.%20they%20were%20either%20employed%2C%20or%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20data%20from%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20(ILO)%20modelled%20estimates%20show.%20In%20India%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20only%2051.3%20percent%20of%20those%20in%20this%20age%20group%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20in%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%202%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure2.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20this%20difference%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20chasm%20between%20the%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20in%20the%20two%20countries.%20India%20has%20lower%20rates%20of%20both%20male%20and%20female%20labour%20force%20participation%20compared%20to%20China%2C%20but%20the%20gap%20is%20much%20bigger%20for%20female%20LFPRs.%20In%202021%2C%2076.2%20percent%20of%20Indian%20men%20(15-64)%20were%20part%20of%20its%20labour%20force%2C%20and%20in%20China%20this%20share%20was%2080.5%20percent.%20In%20the%20same%20year%2C%20only%2024.6%20percent%20of%20women%20(15-64)%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20in%20India%2C%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%2070.8%20percent%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20difference%20in%20LFPR%20essentially%20means%20that%20in%202021%2C%20while%20there%20were%20986.5%20million%20people%20in%20China%20aged%2015-64%2C%20there%20were%20747.9%20million%20people%20who%20were%20employed%20or%20looking%20for%20employment%2C%20our%20calculations%20show.%20In%20India%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20were%20950.2%20million%20people%20aged%2015-64%20in%202021%2C%20but%20only%20487.9%20million%20were%20part%20of%20the%20labour%20force%20(Figure%203).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20wider%20gap%20in%20FLFPR%2C%20this%20difference%20was%20starker%20for%20the%20female%20population%2C%20our%20calculations%20show.%20In%202021%2C%20China%20had%20an%20estimated%20478.3%20million%20women%20aged%2015-64%2C%20and%20its%20female%20labour%20force%20was%20an%20estimated%20338.6%20million%20in%20size.%20In%20India%2C%20the%20female%20labour%20force%20was%20only%20112.8%20million%20in%20comparison%20even%20though%20it%20had%20458.2%20million%20women%20in%20that%20age%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EFigure%203%3A%20Estimated%20working%20age%20(15-64%20years)%20population%20and%20labour%20force%2C%20India%20and%20China%2C%202021%20(in%20millions)%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Cthead%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3Cth%3ERatio%20(China%2FIndia)%3C%2Fth%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fthead%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EPopulation%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E986.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E950.2%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1.04%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3ELFPR%20(in%20percent)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E75.8%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E51.3%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3ELabour%20force%20size%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E747.9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E487.9%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E1.53%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EFemale%20population%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E478.3%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E458.2%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1.04%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EFLFPR%20(in%20percent)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E70.8%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E24.6%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3EFemale%20labour%20force%20size%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E338.6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E112.8%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E3.00%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EMale%20population%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E508.2%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E492.1%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E1.03%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3EMLFPR%20(in%20percent)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E80.5%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E76.2%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3EMale%20labour%20force%20size%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E409.2%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E375.1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cspan%3E1.09%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3Ccaption%3ESource%3A%20Population%20numbers%20from%20UN%20Population%20Estimates.%3Cbr%3E%5CnLabour%20force%20participation%20rates%20based%20in%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20modelled%20estimates%20via%20The%20World%20Bank%3C%2Fcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20while%20India%E2%80%99s%20working%20age%20demographic%20group%20was%20almost%20comparable%20in%20size%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%2C%20its%20labour%20force%20was%20significantly%20smaller%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20its%20much%20lower%20rates%20of%20female%20labour%20force%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20when%20is%20India%20likely%20to%20overtake%20China%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20assume%20constant%20LFPR%20rates%20as%20the%20most%20recent%20ones%20for%20both%20countries%2C%20it%20will%20take%20another%2027%20years%20for%20that%20to%20happen.%20It%20is%20only%20in%202051%20when%20India%20will%20have%20more%20people%20in%20the%20labour%20force%20(15-64)%20than%20China%20(assuming%20everything%20else%20remains%20constant).%20These%20calculations%20are%20based%20on%20UN%20populations%20estimates%20available%20for%20all%20years%20up%20till%202100.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%204%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdn%2F16062023%2Flabour-force-estimation%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E(To%20view%20this%20visualisation%20fully%20on%20your%20device%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdn%2F16062023%2Flabour-force-estimation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPR%20were%20to%20increase%20to%2060%20percent%2C%20this%20could%20happen%20by%202040.%20(Users%20can%20enter%20different%20LFPR%20values%20in%20Figure%204%20to%20see%20how%20this%20timeline%20changes%20in%20different%20scenarios).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%E2%80%99s%20labour%20force%20to%20exceed%20China%E2%80%99s%20in%20absolute%20numbers%20by%202030%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20LFPR%20would%20need%20to%20increase%20sharply%20from%20the%20current%20level%20of%20roughly%2058%20percent%20(the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rate%20by%20usual%20status%20for%20the%2015-64%20age%20group%20as%20estimated%20by%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%2C%202021-22)%20to%2071%20percent%20for%20the%20next%20seven%20years.%20There%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20such%20drastic%20improvement%20could%20be%20achieved%20in%20a%20short%20span%20of%20time.%20Any%20increase%20in%20overall%20LFPR%20is%20contingent%20upon%20on%20improving%20the%20share%20of%20women%20in%20the%20labour%20force%2C%20which%20is%20not%20impossible%2C%20but%20would%20need%20a%20dedicated%20set%20of%20comprehensive%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20demographic%20and%20gender%20dividends%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mere%20existence%20of%20a%20larger%20working%20age%20population%20does%20not%20constitute%20a%20demographic%20dividend.%20For%20it%20to%20be%20a%20dividend%2C%20first%2C%20the%20working%20age%20population%20must%20be%20in%20the%20labour%20force.%20Second%2C%20they%20must%20be%20productively%20employed.%20Otherwise%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20working%20age%20group%20who%20are%20not%20productively%20employed%20can%20represent%20a%20huge%20challenge%20as%20the%20unfulfilled%20need%20for%20livelihood%20opportunities%20is%20a%20sure-fire%20recipe%20for%20discontent%20and%20unrest%20which%20can%20enhance%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%20a%20jobs%20crisis%2C%20as%20roughly%205.5%20million%20new%20jobs%20that%20the%20country%20needs%20are%20not%20getting%20created%2C%20which%20makes%20agriculture%20the%20sector%20of%20last%20resort%20for%20people%20to%20eke%20out%20a%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20India%20is%20already%20grappling%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdecoding-womens-labour-force-participation-in-2021-22-what-the-periodic-labour-force-survey-shows%2F%5C%22%3Elow%20female%20LFPRs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20reason%20responsible%20for%20the%20low%20levels%20is%20undercounting%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20economic%20work%20on%20family%20enterprises.%20Accounting%20for%20this%20work%20raises%20LFPR%20estimates%2C%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20official%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Feconomicsurvey%2Fdoc%2Feschapter%2Fechap06.pdf%5C%22%3EEconomic%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20attempted%20to%20do.%20While%20recognizing%20women%E2%80%99s%20(unpaid)%20contribution%20to%20family%20enterprises%20is%20very%20important%2C%20it%20is%20not%20a%20substitute%20for%20paid%20work%2C%20the%20opportunities%20for%20which%20are%20not%20growing%20as%20rapidly%20as%20needed.%20There%20is%20dire%20need%20for%20expansion%20of%20rural%20non-farm%20employment%2C%20both%20for%20men%20and%20women%2C%20but%20especially%20crucial%20for%20women%20as%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20travel%20long%20distances%20to%20access%20work%2C%20due%20to%20their%20predominant%20responsibility%20for%20domestic%20chores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20growth%20was%20in%20no%20small%20measure%20due%20to%20one%20element%20of%20their%20economic%20reforms%3A%20the%20expansion%20of%20rural%20industry%20via%20the%20Township%20and%20Village%20Enterprises%20(TVEs)%20that%20absorbed%20its%20massive%20workforce%20in%20small%2C%20labour%20intensive%2C%20nonfarm%20work%20opportunities.%20Between%201978%20(the%20start%20of%20the%20economic%20reforms)%20and%201995%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20rural%20industries%20grew%20over%2020%20percent%20per%20year%2C%20raising%20their%20share%20in%20industrial%20production%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elibrary.imf.org%2Fdisplay%2Fbook%2F9781557755421%2Fch013.xml%5C%22%3E3%20percent%20in%201971%20to%2030%20percent%20in%201990%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20bus%20that%20India%20seems%20to%20be%20missing.%20If%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20remunerative%20work%20for%20young%20people%20and%20women%2C%20a%20very%20large%20potential%20pool%20of%20talent%20will%20remain%20un-%20or%20underutilized%20and%20the%20much-vaunted%20demographic%20dividend%20will%20remain%20illusory%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESkill%20differences%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20big%20contrast%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20training%2Fskill%20differences%20of%20the%20population.%20While%20in%20both%20countries%2C%20gross%20enrolment%20ratio%20for%20tertiary%20education%20(GETR)%20has%20been%20increasing%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GETR%20in%202021%20was%20roughly%20half%20that%20of%20China%20in%202021%20(Figure%205).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFigure%205%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20align%3D%5C%22center%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fviz.ceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fdata-narrative%2F16062023%2Ffigure5.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3ELooks%20like%20your%20browser%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20support%20iframes.%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20China%20have%20a%20higher%20GETR%20compared%20to%20India%20for%20both%20men%20and%20women%2C%20but%20the%20relative%20difference%20has%20also%20increased%20over%20recent%20years.%20In%202015%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20GETR%20was%201.7%20times%20that%20of%20India.%20By%202021%2C%20it%20was%20twice%20the%20level%20of%20India.%20The%20female%20gap%20remained%20roughly%20constant%20over%20the%20period%20(from%201.9%20to%202.1)%2C%20whereas%20the%20male%20gap%20increased%20from%201.6%20to%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20Elephant-Dragon%20Tango%20will%20continue%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20sober%20reflection%20reveals%20that%20while%20India%20will%20become%20the%20most%20populous%20country%2C%20it%20is%20not%20about%20to%20overtake%20China%20in%20terms%20of%20a%20bigger%20and%20more%20educated%20labour%20force.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20continued%20growth%20of%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20is%20free%20of%20its%20own%20set%20of%20challenges.%20In%20addition%20to%20battling%20geo-political%20challenges%20to%20its%20global%20expansion%20plans%2C%20China%20has%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20shrinking%20labour%20force%2C%20ageing%20population%20and%20boosting%20productivity%20growth.%20How%20acutely%20these%20challenges%20affect%20the%20Chinese%20rate%20of%20growth%20is%20a)%20a%20subject%20matter%20for%20another%20article%20and%20b)%20something%20only%20time%20will%20tell.%20This%20piece%20focuses%20on%20the%20Elephant-Dragon%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20female%20LFPRs%2C%20not%20only%20via%20correctly%20measuring%20women%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20but%20via%20creation%20of%20an%20ecosystem%20that%20provides%20remunerative%20and%20sustainable%20livelihoods%20close%20to%20home%20(read%20rural%20nonfarm%20employment)%20and%20investing%20in%20an%20educated%2C%20skilled%20and%20healthy%20workforce%20should%20be%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20priority%2C%20based%20on%20its%20own%20demographic%20reality%2C%20not%20just%20because%20of%20a%20presumed%20competition%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshwini%20Deshpande%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20ashwini.deshpande%40ashoka.edu.in.%20Akshi%20Chawla%20is%20editor%2C%20CEDA%2C%20and%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20akshi.chawla%40ashoka.edu.in.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fthe-elephant-is-set-to-overtake-the-dragon-or-is-it%2F%5C%22%3ECEDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690447209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27133636%2F6283735999_47c3124b38_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-china-population-labour-force%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22...if%20we%20assume%20the%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20for%20both%20countries%20will%20remain%20constant%2C%20and%20so%20will%20other%20factors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Findia-china-population-labour-force%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20PM's%20%5C%22Red%20Diary%5C%22%20Barb%2C%20Ashok%20Gehlot's%20%5C%22Red%20Tomatoes%2C%20Red%20Flag%5C%22%20Retort%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20suspense%20over%20the%20%26quot%3Bred%20diary%26quot%3B%20in%20Rajasthan's%20political%20corridors%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20today%20claimed%20that%20the%20secrets%20in%20the%20diary%20will%20ruin%20the%20ruling%20Congress%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Assembly%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sharp%20comeback%2C%20Chief%20Minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20said%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20can%20see%20an%20%26quot%3Bimaginary%20red%20diary%26quot%3B%2C%20but%20not%20red%20tomatoes%20and%20red%20cylinders%2C%20skyrocketing%20prices%20of%20which%20have%20hit%20kitchen%20budgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20rally%20at%20Sikar%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20mocked%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20%26quot%3Bmohabbat%20ki%20dukaan%26quot%3B%20slogan%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20latest%20product%20of%20'loot%20ki%20dukaan%2C%20jhoot%20ki%20dukaan'%20(store%20of%20loot%20and%20lies)%20is%20the%20red%20diary.%20It%20is%20being%20said%20that%20the%20it%20contains%20secrets%20about%20Congress's%20corruption.%20This%20red%20diary%20will%20ruin%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20polls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20targeted%20the%20Ashok%20Gehlot%20government%20over%20paper%20leaks%20in%20job%20recruitment%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHitting%20back%2C%20Mr%20Gehlot%20said%20at%20a%20state%20government%20event%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20red%20diary%20is%20an%20imagination.%20There%20is%20no%20red%20diary.%20He%20can%20see%20the%20red%20diary%2C%20but%20not%20red%20cylinders%20and%20red%20tomatoes.%20He%20can't%20see%20the%20faces%20of%20people%20that%20have%20turned%20red%20due%20to%20price%20rise.%20People%20will%20show%20him%20the%20red%20flag%20in%20the%20elections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fashok-gehlot-rajasthan-elections-rajendra-singh-gudha-red-diary-what-secrets-does-rajasthans-red-diary-contain-claims-and-counters-4239031%5C%22%3Ered%20diary%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20top%20talking%20point%20in%20Rajasthan%20following%20dramatic%20events%20in%20Assembly%20last%20week.%20Rajendra%20Singh%20Gudha%2C%20a%20Congress%20MLA%20recently%20sacked%20following%20his%20remarks%20on%20the%20state%20government's%20%26quot%3Bfailure%26quot%3B%20to%20ensure%20security%20of%20women%2C%20walked%20into%20the%20Assembly%20with%20a%20red%20diary%20that%20he%20claimed%20could%20%26quot%3Bexpose%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gehlot.%20He%20was%20marshalled%20out%20of%20the%20House.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESensing%20the%20political%20opportunity%2C%20the%20BJP%20claimed%20that%20the%20red%20diary%20contains%20secrets%20the%20revelation%20of%20which%20can%20potentially%20wipe%20out%20the%20political%20existence%20of%20many%20leaders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gudha%20has%20claimed%20this%20diary%20contains%20details%20of%20pay-offs%20made%20by%20the%20Gehlot%20camp%20to%20MLAs%2C%20Independents%20and%20others%20to%20save%20his%20government%20during%20the%202020%20rebellion%20led%20by%20Sachin%20Pilot.%20The%20diary%20also%20contains%20details%20of%20payoffs%20by%20the%20Congress%20to%20ensure%20the%20victory%20of%20its%20candidates%20despite%20a%20tough%20contest%20from%20BJP-backed%20Independent%20and%20media%20baron%20Subhash%20Chandra%2C%20he%20has%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20has%20trashed%20Mr%20Gudha's%20claims%2C%20calling%20them%20fabricated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister's%20rally%20today%20was%20held%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-narendra-modi-ashok-gehlot-rajasthan-elections-ahead-of-pm-modis-trip-to-poll-bound-rajasthan-ashok-gehlots-big-charge-4243961%5C%22%3Epublic%20squabbling%20between%20his%20office%20and%20Chief%20Minister%20Gehlot%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20latter%20alleged%20that%20his%20speech%20had%20been%20removed%20from%20an%20event's%20itinerary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20social%20media%20post%2C%20Mr%20Gehlot%20said%20this%20morning%20that%20he%20could%20only%20welcome%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20on%20Twitter%20since%20his%20speech%20via%20videoconference%20had%20been%20cancelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%20you%20are%20visiting%20Rajasthan.%20Your%20office%20PMO%20has%20removed%20my%20pre-scheduled%203-minute%20address%20from%20the%20programme%2C%20so%20I%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20welcome%20you%20through%20speech%2C%20so%20I%20heartily%20welcome%20you%20to%20Rajasthan%20through%20this%20tweet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Minister%20also%20listed%20his%20demands%20for%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister's%20office%20responded%20that%20it%20was%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20that%20said%20he%20would%20skip%20the%20event%20due%20to%20a%20leg%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20accordance%20with%20protocol%2C%20you%20have%20been%20duly%20invited%20and%20your%20speech%20was%20also%20slotted.%20But%2C%20your%20office%20said%20you%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20join.%20During%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi's%20previous%20visits%20as%20well%20you%20have%20always%20been%20invited%20and%20you%20have%20also%20graced%20those%20programmes%20with%20your%20presence.%20You%20are%20most%20welcome%20to%20join%20today's%20programme.%20Your%20name%20is%20very%20much%20there%20on%20the%20plaque%20of%20the%20development%20works%20as%20well.%20Unless%20you%20have%20any%20physical%20discomfort%20owing%20to%20your%20recent%20injury%2C%20your%20presence%20will%20be%20deeply%20valued%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20PMO%20tweeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoubling%20down%2C%20Mr%20Gehlot%20shared%20letters%20as%20proof%20that%20he%20was%20to%20attend%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20programme%20remotely%20but%20the%20plans%20changed%20last%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRespected%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20your%20office%20has%20taken%20cognizance%20of%20my%20tweet%20but%20they%20probably%20have%20not%20been%20made%20aware%20of%20the%20facts.%20My%20address%20was%20kept%20in%20the%20proposed%20minute-to-minute%20programme%20sent%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Health.%20Last%20night%20I%20was%20again%20informed%20that%20I%20would%20not%20be%20addressing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20Hindi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20office%20had%20informed%20the%20government%20of%20India%20that%20as%20per%20the%20opinion%20of%20doctors%2C%20due%20to%20a%20leg%20injury%2C%20I%20would%20attend%20the%20program%20through%20video%20conferencing%20and%20my%20ministers%20would%20reach%20the%20venue.%20Even%20now%20I%20will%20be%20involved%20in%20this%20program%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20on%20non-interactive%20mode%2C%20through%20video%20conferencing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20while%20addressing%20farmers%20in%20Sikar%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAshok%20Gehlot%20was%20supposed%20to%20attend%20the%20programme%20but%20could%20not%20due%20to%20ill%20health.%20I%20pray%20for%20his%20speedy%20recovery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fthey-changed-name-from-upa-to-india-because-pms-jibe-in-rajasthan-4244459%5C%22%3Etargeted%20the%20Opposition%20front%20INDIA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20they%20changed%20the%20name%20from%20UPA%20to%20INDIA%20to%20%26quot%3Bhide%20wrongdoings%20of%20the%20past%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690447020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2F7ffpl5lo_narendra-modi-ashok-gehlot-pti_625x300_01_November_22.jpg%22%