EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2026%2C%20rectified%20an%20inadvertent%20error%20by%20which%20it%20had%20on%20Monday%2C%20July%2024%2C%20disposed%20of%20a%20plea%20on%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20related%20to%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20and%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20temple%20at%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fasis-scientific-survey-begins-at-gyanvapi-mosque-amidst-heavy-security%5C%22%3Ehalted%20the%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20mosque%20until%205%20pm%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2026%2C%20ordered%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court.%20The%20survey%20by%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20was%20ordered%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20error%20was%20pointed%20out%20by%20Huzefa%20Ahmadi%2C%20representing%20the%20Committee%20of%20Management%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20that%20the%20court%20had%20inadvertently%20disposed%20of%20the%20main%20plea%20instead%20of%20the%20interlocutory%20application%2C%20which%20only%20sought%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20ASI%20survey.%20The%20main%20plea%20referred%20to%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Committee%20challenging%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20its%20Order%207%20Rule%2011%20CPC%20(Code%20of%20Civil%20Procedure)%20plea%20against%20the%20maintainability%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Worshippers%E2%80%99%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-clarifies-order-in-gyanvapi-case-says-mosque-committees-petition-challenging-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-233643%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ahmadi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20correction%20needed%20in%20the%20Monday%20order.%20Your%20Lordships%20accidentally%20disposed%20the%20SLP.%20We%20had%20moved%20for%20the%20IA%20%5Binterlocutory%20application%5D.%20The%20only%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20matter%20is%20going%20on%20before%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%20The%20SLP%20(special%20leave%20petition)%20is%20against%20an%20Order%207%20Rule%2011%20issue%E2%80%A6that%20has%20been%20disposed%20of%20but%20we%20never%20argued%20on%20that.%20We%20only%20argued%20on%20the%20ASI%20survey%20point.%20Now%20before%20the%20Allahabad%20HC%2C%20it%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20our%20appeal%20has%20been%20dismissed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20hearing%20Ahmadi%E2%80%99s%20explanation%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20promptly%20corrected%20the%20order%2C%20clarifying%20that%20what%20was%20disposed%20of%20was%20the%20interlocutory%20petition%20and%20not%20the%20special%20leave%20petition%20as%20assumed%20earlier.%20He%20then%20ordered%20the%20court%20staff%20to%20delete%20Paragraph%2010%20of%20the%20order%2C%20which%20led%20to%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20the%20Masjid%20Committee%20had%20moved%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20challenging%20the%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20filed%20by%20five%20Hindu%20women%2C%20who%20sought%20the%20right%20to%20worship%20inside%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20compound.%20The%20plea%20was%20filed%20under%C2%A0Order%207%20Rule%2011%20CPC.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Masjid%20Committee%20had%20to%20move%20the%20high%20court%20because%20the%20same%20plea%20was%20turned%20down%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court.%20The%20district%20court%20held%20that%20the%20Hindu%20petitioners%20cannot%20be%20barred%20from%20worshipping%20rights%20under%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%2C%20The%20Waqf%20Act%201995%2C%20and%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Act%2C%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20then%20dismissed%20Masjid%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20upholding%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Hindu%20petitioners%20filed%20an%20application%20before%20a%20trial%20court%20requesting%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20by%20the%20ASI%2C%20which%20was%20allowed%20on%20July%2021.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20then%20stayed%20the%20trial%20court%20order%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20survey%20will%20be%20on%20hold%20until%205%20pm%20on%20July%2026%20to%20allow%20the%20Masjid%20committee%20to%20challenge%20the%20survey%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690437910000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-committees-plea-against-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-clarifies-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20in%20its%20previous%20order%20had%20inadvertently%20disposed%20of%20the%20main%20plea%20instead%20of%20the%20interlocutory%20application%2C%20which%20only%20sought%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20survey%20by%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-committees-plea-against-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-clarifies-sc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Examining%20Various%20Facets%20of%20Photography%20in%20the%20South%20Asian%20Context%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24154209%2Faziz-acharki-Zf14BckA1JA-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ERahaab%20Allana%E2%80%99s%20edited%20volume%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20lens-based%20practices%20in%20South%20Asia%20comes%20at%20a%20moment%20of%20introspection%20for%20photography%20as%20a%20practice%20that%20has%20seen%20several%20turns%20in%20its%20nearly%20200-year-old%20biography.%20Professionally%20too%2C%20this%20is%20a%20reflective%20moment%20for%20the%20editor%20who%20in%20the%20introduction%2C%20ruminates%20over%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20of%20work%20produced%20by%20the%20Alkazi%20Collection%20of%20Photography%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20including%20exhibitions%2C%20conferences%2C%20books%20and%20other%20events%20from%20within%20and%20beyond%20its%20own%20archive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20%E2%80%98unframing%E2%80%99%20that%20the%20volume%20offers%20has%20to%20do%20with%20identifying%20and%20unpacking%2C%20understanding%20and%20critiquing%20the%20archival%2C%20institutional%2C%20theoretical%2C%20exhibitionary%20and%20artistic%20frameworks%20that%20have%20defined%20photography%20in%20South%20Asia.%20At%20stake%20is%20a%20redefinition%20of%20both%2C%20vernacular%20photography%20from%20the%20non%20Euro-American%20world%20as%20well%20as%20what%20is%20understood%20as%20South%20Asian%20lens%20based%20visual%20culture%20at%20large.%20As%20Allana%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20volume%20presents%20photography%20as%20both%20an%20original%20media%20that%20can%20assume%20hybrid%20form%2C%20and%20as%20a%20political%2C%20historical%20and%20social%20resource%20that%20has%20radically%20expanded%20our%20understanding%20of%20artistic%20and%20activist%20engagement%20in%20colonial%20and%20postcolonial%20%E2%80%9CSouth%20Asia%E2%80%9D.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20307px)%2085vw%2C%20307px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24153522%2FA1mkTOaG5uL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22307%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24153522%2FA1mkTOaG5uL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20713w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24153522%2FA1mkTOaG5uL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-214x300.jpg%20214w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664763%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22431%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EUnframed%3A%20Discovering%20Image%20Practices%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EEdited%20by%20Rahaab%20Allana%3Cbr%3EAlkazi%20Collection%20of%20Photography%20and%20Harper%20Design%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%E2%80%99s%20essays%20appear%20under%20five%20sections%2C%20each%20informing%20the%20reader%20on%20photography%E2%80%99s%20origins%2C%20operations%20and%20impact%20in%20the%20region.%20They%20range%20between%20explorations%20of%20the%20self%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20colonial%20context%2C%20the%20technologies%20of%20image%20production%20and%20circuits%20of%20representation%2C%20contemporary%20curatorial%20methodologies%20and%20national%20cultural%20politics%20and%20histories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20book%20does%20not%20claim%20to%20be%20exhaustive%20in%20addressing%20all%20photographic%20history%20in%20the%20region%2C%20it%20is%20an%20ambitious%20work%20towards%20a%20counter%20discursive%20space%20that%20departs%20from%20known%20theoretical%20Euro-American%20models%20of%20understanding%20the%20camera%E2%80%99s%20operations.%20It%20is%20hoped%20that%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20shall%20see%20subsequent%20volumes%20that%20further%20address%20the%20currently%20overlooked%20issues%20of%20intersectionality%2C%20commerce%20and%20pedagogy%20among%20others%2C%20that%20shape%20our%20photography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUnframed%20%3C%2Fem%3Eacknowledges%20the%20medium%20specificity%20of%20the%20camera%2C%20engaging%20with%20technological%2C%20aesthetic%20and%20institutional%20dimensions%20of%20photography%20within%20the%20larger%20socio-political%20terrain%20that%20it%20affects.%20The%20essays%20seek%20to%20interrogate%20how%20photography%20has%20addressed%2C%20affirmed%20and%20countered%20global%20assumptions%20about%20South%20Asia%2C%20how%20these%20countries%20are%20home%20and%20nation%20to%20diverse%20ethnic%2C%20linguistic%20and%20cultural%20communities%2C%20geopolitically%20bounded%2C%20but%20also%20challenged.%20The%20state%20is%20repeatedly%20evoked%20for%20its%20roles%20as%20the%20archivist%2C%20laboratory%2C%20pedagogue%2C%20patron%2C%20critic%20and%20censoring%20agency%20of%20photography.%20Essays%20on%20photographies%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbouring%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Pakistan%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Nepal%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Myanmar%20%E2%80%93%20draw%20new%20interconnections%20through%20the%20substratum%20of%20digital%20networks%20that%20cut%20across%20known%20realities%20of%20animosity%20and%20cooperation.%20These%20are%20illustrative%20of%20the%20true%20democratisation%20of%20the%20camera%20in%20a%20transnational%20space.%20As%20a%20volume%20that%20is%20chiefly%20concerned%20with%20how%20power%20is%20challenged%20by%20the%20fluidity%20and%20disobedience%20that%20photography%20offers%2C%20the%20essays%20highlight%20anomalies%20to%20expected%20differences%20of%20gender%2C%20caste%20and%20class%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20each%20of%20its%20five%20sections%2C%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20addresses%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20viewing%20gaze%20and%20its%20expectation%20from%20photographs%20to%20meet%20the%20claims%20of%20identity%20and%20selfhood%20in%20personal%2C%20local%2C%20national%20and%20transnational%20contexts.%20The%20category%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98vernacular%E2%80%99%20interestingly%20subsumes%20the%20plebeian%20and%20the%20princely%20photographer%20from%20South%20Asia%2C%20discussed%20in%20the%20early%20essays%20of%20the%20book.%20In%20his%20essay%2C%20Allana%20dwells%20on%20the%20exhibition%20%3Cem%3EEphemeral%3A%20New%20Futures%20for%20Passing%20Images%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20Serendipity%20Arts%20Festival%20in%20Goa%20in%202018%20mulling%20over%20possible%20iterations%20of%20vernacular%20photography%20practiced%20locally%2C%20while%20Mrinalini%20Venkateswaran%20examines%20the%20nineteenth%20century%20archive%20of%20Sawai%20Ram%20Singh%20II%20from%20Jaipur%2C%20the%20first%20photographer%20prince%20to%20use%20the%20modern%20camera.%20Other%20practices%20such%20as%20the%20ethnographic%20works%20of%20James%20Henry%20Green%20(1893%20%E2%80%93%201975)%20in%20Burma%20resonate%20with%20the%20photographs%20from%20Ceylon%20in%20the%20essays%20by%20David%20Odo%20and%20Ismeth%20Raheem%20respectively.%20The%20photographer%20Lionel%20Wendt%E2%80%99s%20(1900-1944)%20experiments%20in%20a%20modern%20photographic%20styles%20presenting%20a%20counter%20gaze%20to%20colonial%20stereo%20typification%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98native%E2%80%99%20in%20Ceylon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20inclined%20to%20try%20and%20locate%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20amidst%20other%20recently%20published%20edited%20volumes%20on%20photography%2C%20namely%20%3Cem%3EPhotography%20in%20India%3A%20From%20Archives%20to%20Contemporary%20Practice%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20edited%20by%20Aileen%20Blaney%20and%20Chinar%20Shah%20(2020)%2C%20%3Cem%3EPhotography%20in%20India%3A%20A%20Visual%20History%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20the%201850s%20to%20the%20Present%2C%20by%20Diva%20Gujral%20and%20Nathaniel%20Gaskell%20(2019)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EPoints%20of%20View%3A%20Defining%20Moments%20of%20Photography%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20edited%20by%20Gayatri%20Sinha%20(2021).%20It%20shares%20overlapping%20concerns%20with%20these%20closely%20timed%20volumes%2C%20yet%20its%20focus%20on%20the%20socio-political%20flux%20that%20complicates%20South%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20political%20identity%20sets%20it%20apart.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20essays%20by%20Bakirathi%20Mani%20on%20diasporic%20Indian%20identity%2C%20or%20Hammad%20Nasar%20on%20the%20overall%20status%20of%20art%20practice%20in%20Pakistan%20offer%20wider%20contexts%20to%20locate%20photography%2C%20without%20addressing%20the%20medium%20of%20the%20camera%20in%20particular.%20Such%20inclusions%20allow%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20identify%20the%20larger%20frameworks%20that%20construct%20South%20Asian%20visuality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24153712%2Fdownload-4.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22298%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664764%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22398%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERahaab%20Allana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20title%20of%20the%20volume%20claims%20to%20%E2%80%98discover%E2%80%99%20new%20image%20practices%2C%20which%20it%20does%20along%20with%20new%20writing%20on%20photography%20from%20South%20Asia%2C%20but%20it%20posits%20these%20amidst%20established%20publications%20that%20mainly%20address%20Indian%20photography.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20older%2C%20landmark%20essays%20that%20have%20defined%20the%20discipline%2C%20say%20by%20the%20authors%20Christopher%20Pinney%20and%20Sudhir%20Mahadevan%2C%20locate%2C%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%98frame%E2%80%99%20or%20subsume%20the%20South%20Asian%20photographic%20context%E2%80%99s%20dialogue%20with%20Euro-American%20theoretical%20investigations.%20What%20emerges%20is%20a%20possible%20set%20of%20new%20methodologies%20for%20examining%20photography.%20Pinney%20is%20known%20for%20his%20groundbreaking%20work%20on%20colonial%20and%20studio%20based%20photography%20in%20India%20in%20his%20books%20%3Cem%3ECamera%20Indica%3A%20the%20Social%20Life%20of%20Photographs%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1997)%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Coming%20of%20Photography%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2008)%2C%20while%20Mahadevan%20writes%20on%20photography%E2%80%99s%20technological%20and%20ontological%20affiliations%20with%20cinema.%20Gopesa%20Paquette%E2%80%99s%20essay%20explores%20the%20possibility%20of%20photography%E2%80%99s%20dialogue%20with%20classical%20aesthetics%20from%20within%20South%20Asia%2C%20ranging%20from%20Darshan%20to%20Rasa%20theory%2C%20opening%20new%20ways%20of%20re-looking%20at%20our%20lens%20based%20practices.%20The%20late%20Aveek%20Sen%E2%80%99s%20lecture%20from%202010%20titled%20%E2%80%98Between%20Blue%20Rocks%E2%80%99%20addresses%20the%20important%20exhibition%20%3Cem%3EWhere%20Three%20Dreams%20Cross%3A%20150%20Years%20of%20Photography%20from%20India%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20held%20in%20London%20and%20Switzerland.%20Sen%20uses%20the%20literary%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20commenting%20on%20the%20photographic%20flows%20across%20these%20three%20countries.%20From%20the%20same%20exhibition%E2%80%99s%20catalogue%20is%20Geeta%20Kapur%E2%80%99s%20insightful%20commentary%20on%20the%20family%20as%20a%20subject%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20key%20modern%20and%20contemporary%20photographers%20Umrao%20Singh%20Sher-Gil%2C%20Ketaki%20Sheth%2C%20Pablo%20Bartholomew%20and%20Dayanita%20Singh.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20%3Cem%3EUnframed%3C%2Fem%3E%20urges%20the%20reader%20to%20examine%20the%20rationale%20behind%20the%20political%20cartographies%20that%20divide%20South%20Asia%20within%20itself%2C%20in%20fact%20Saloni%20Mathur%E2%80%99s%20essay%20concludes%20Partition%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98method%E2%80%99%20in%20social%20research%20that%20more%20broadly%20embeds%20photography%20amidst%20other%20visual%20art%20practices%20from%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20essays%20and%20interviews%20of%20the%20book%20analyse%20photography%20within%20larger%20discourses%20on%20institutional%2C%20exhibitory%20and%20curatorial%20initiatives%20in%20India%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Myanmar%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20identifying%20ventures%20such%20as%20the%20Triennale%20and%20the%20other%20international%20art%20projects%20as%20formative%20junctures%20for%20photography%E2%80%99s%20public%20manifestations.%20Other%20histories%20of%20photography%20in%20print%20evidence%20the%20inter-ocularity%20of%20visual%20genres%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20the%20essay%20by%20Sabeena%20Gadihoke%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3EIllustrated%20Weekly%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%20that%20ran%20between%20the%201930s%20and%2090s%2C%20Omar%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20essay%20on%20photographic%20postcards%20and%20Sukanya%20Baskar%E2%80%99s%20re-examination%20of%20the%20global%20exhibition%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EFamily%20of%20Man%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1955)%2C%20chiefly%20through%20its%20catalogue%20and%20press%20archives.%20Inter-ocularity%20re-appears%20as%20the%20central%20theme%20of%20an%20interview%20between%20Allana%20and%20Ashmina%20Ranjit%2C%20a%20performance%20artist%20from%20Nepal%2C%20her%20political%20activism%20taking%20form%20through%20the%20convergence%20of%20these%20two%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20book%E2%80%99s%20design%20is%20to%20be%20appreciated%20for%20its%20attention%20to%20detail%2C%20the%20treatment%20of%20images%20that%20level%20between%20colour%20and%20black%20and%20white%2C%20and%20the%20non-hardcover%2C%20academic%20format%20inviting%20serious%20engagement%20instead%20of%20the%20leisurely%20perusal%20of%20a%20coffee-table%20publication.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20text%20is%20granted%20a%20certain%20%E2%80%98visual%E2%80%99%20space%20to%20foster%20meandered%20meaning%20making%2C%20an%20unusual%20but%20effective%20strategy%20for%20a%20book%20on%20photography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESuryanandini%20Narain%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Visual%20Studies%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690437646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24154209%2Faziz-acharki-Zf14BckA1JA-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexamining-various-facets-of-photography-in-the-south-asian-context%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Through%20a%20series%20of%20essays%2C%20a%20new%20volume%20examines%20the%20works%20of%20contemporary%20and%20old%20photographers%20to%20understand%20and%20redefine%20%E2%80%98vernacular%E2%80%99%20work%20in%20the%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fexamining-various-facets-of-photography-in