20Costa%20Mesa%2C%20California%2C%20on%20July%2014%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Bersebach%2FMediaNews%20Group%2FOrange%20County%20Register%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EProsecutors%20say%20a%20family%20that%20made%20%247.6%20million%20from%20recycling%20defrauded%20the%20state%20of%20California.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20family%2C%20based%20in%20Southern%20California%2C%20is%20accused%20of%20recycling%20materials%20purchased%20in%20Arizona.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMore%20than%20%241%20million%20worth%20of%20%26quot%3Billegally%20imported%20beverage%20containers%26quot%3B%20was%20found%2C%20a%20statement%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20California%20family%20that%20earned%20millions%20of%20dollars%20just%20by%20recycling%20cans%20and%20bottles%20has%20now%20been%20accused%20of%20multiple%20felonies%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20years%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foag.ca.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fattachments%2Fpress-docs%2FFelony%2520Complaint%2520for%2520Arrest%2520Warrant.pdf%5C%22%3Efelony%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20this%20month%2C%20state%20prosecutors%20charged%20eight%20family%20members%20in%20Riverside%20County%20with%20defrauding%20the%20state%20by%20importing%20used%20bottles%20and%20cans%20from%20Arizona%20%E2%80%94%20some%20178%20tons%20in%208%20months%20%E2%80%94%20and%20recycling%20them%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recycling%20operation%20earned%20the%20family%20%247.6%20million%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foag.ca.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fattorney-general-bonta-and-calrecycle-announce-charges-seizures-riverside-county%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20office%20of%20California's%20Attorney%20General%2C%20Rob%20Bonta.%20Investigators%20also%20found%20a%20stash%20of%20%26quot%3Billegally%20imported%20beverage%20containers%26quot%3B%20worth%20another%20%241%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20purchases%20a%20plastic%20or%20aluminum%20bottle%20in%20California%2C%20they%20typically%20pay%20an%20extra%205%20to%2010%20cents%20in%20%26quot%3BCalifornia%20Redemption%20Value%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20CRV%2C%20which%20the%20consumer%20can%20get%20back%20by%20returning%20the%20items%20to%20one%20of%20the%20state's%20more%20than%201%2C200%20recycling%20centers.%20Arizona%20has%20no%20such%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia's%20recycling%20program%20is%20funded%20by%20consumers%2C%20and%20helps%20protect%20our%20environment%20and%20our%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20Bonta%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20who%20try%20to%20undermine%20its%20integrity%20through%20criminal%20operations%20will%20be%20held%20accountable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20criminal%20complaint%2C%20prosecutors%20accused%20family%20members%20of%20unlawfully%20conspiring%20to%20commit%20grand%20theft%20and%20defrauding%20the%20California%20recycling%20program%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bchronic%20and%20ongoing%20basis%26quot%3B%20by%20seeking%20reimbursement%20for%20out-of-state%20containers%20and%20containers%20that%20had%20already%20been%20redeemed%20within%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFelony%20grand%20theft%20in%20California%20is%20punishable%20by%20up%20to%20three%20years%20in%20state%20prison.%20Redeeming%20out-of-state%20containers%20to%20the%20degree%20the%20family%20is%20accused%20could%20increase%20the%20sentence%20by%20another%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20documents%20did%20not%20identify%20an%20attorney%20for%20the%20defendants%2C%20who%20have%20not%20been%20convicted%20of%20a%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20six%20people%20were%20charged%20in%20a%20similar%20Arizona-to-California%20recycling%20operation%20that%20prosecutors%20said%20netted%20more%20than%20%2410%20million%20by%20fraudulently%20redeeming%20more%20than%20nine%20tons%20of%20empty%20beverage%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2093%2