dhyay%20joined%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20began%20educating%20the%20villagers%20about%20sanitisation%20and%20good%20hygienic%20practices.%20The%20Anti-Malaria%20Cooperative%20Society%20was%20founded%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20the%20village%20level%20in%20India%20at%20Panihati%20on%2024%20March%201918.%20Bandopadhyay%20was%20the%20secretary%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F316087%2Fassam-couple-helps-rural-northeast-india-access-affordable-mental-healthcare-mita%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20the%20helm%20of%20activities%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20encouraged%20cleaning%20ponds%20and%20drains%20in%20the%20village%2C%20clearing%20the%20garbage%20that%20choked%20the%20lakes%20and%20distributing%20mosquito%20nets.%20This%20compelled%20other%20villages%20to%20start%20similar%20associations%20to%20curb%20the%20spread%20of%20malaria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotable%20author%20Amitav%20Ghosh%E2%80%99s%20book%20%E2%80%98The%20Calcutta%20Chromosome%E2%80%99%20details%20bits%20of%20Ross%E2%80%99s%20journey%20while%20shedding%20light%20on%20his%20research%20phase.%20The%20book%20is%20said%20to%20question%20the%20boundaries%20that%20have%20been%20erected%20to%20distinguish%20truth%20from%20fiction%20and%20also%20points%20to%20how%20Bandopadhyay%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20played%20a%20role%20in%20Ross%E2%80%99s%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20disappointment%20at%20not%20finding%20mention%20in%20Ross%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20Bandopadhyay%20went%20on%20to%20start%20The%20Panihati%20Cooperative%20Bank%20in%201927%2C%20two%20years%20after%20which%20he%20passed%20away.%20Today%2C%20as%20there%20have%20been%20several%20strides%20in%20the%20prevention%20and%20cure%20of%20malaria%2C%20we%20remain%20indebted%20to%20Kishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%20for%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F303410%2Firish-teacher-sister-nivedita-cared-for-poor-fought-plague-and-british-rule-in-india-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etremendous%20contribution%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fmalaria%2Fabout%2Fhistory%2Fross.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoss%20and%20the%20Discovery%20that%20Mosquitoes%20Transmit%20Malaria%20Parasites%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Published%20on%2016%20September%202015.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.getbengal.com%2Fdetails%2Fwhy-ronald-ross-bengali-partner-kishori-mohan-not-get-nobel-prize%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhy%20Ronald%20Ross%E2%80%99%20Bengali%20partner%20Kishori%20Mohan%20not%20get%20Nobel%20Prize%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Get%20Bengal%2C%20Published%20on%2028%20November%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeoplepill.com%2Fpeople%2Fkishori-mohan-bandyopadhyay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20People%20Pill.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689686848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F136377747_2849442258642408_8172112795104330360_n-1689681784.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D324194%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kishori%20Mohan%20Bandyopadhyay%20made%20significant%20contributions%20to%20Nobel%20Prize%20winner%20Ronald%20Ross'%20malaria%20research%20as%20his%20lab%20assistant%2C%20but%20never%20received%20due%20recognition%20for%20his%20work.%20The%20Bengali%